               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18190421-243-person2263">
                  HENRY 
                  BEVERLY WAKELING
               <interp inst="t18190421-243-person2263" type="surname" value="BEVERLY WAKELING"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18190421-243-person2263" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18190421-243-person2263" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . On the 23d of April, about eight o'clock in the evening, I was in <placeName id="t18190421-243-crimeloc1357">Drury-lane</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18190421-243-crimeloc1357" type="placeName" value="Drury-lane"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18190421-243-crimeloc1357" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18190421-243-off1355 t18190421-243-crimeloc1357"></join> with Mr. Young; the prisoner and another were following us very close. I felt a hand in my pocket, turned round and collared the prisoner - his companion ran away. My handkerchief was not found; I had it a moment before. I am certain I caught the prisoner's hand in my pocket.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18190421-243-person2264">
                  JOHN 
                  YOUNG
               <interp inst="t18190421-243-person2264" type="surname" value="YOUNG"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18190421-243-person2264" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18190421-243-person2264" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was with Wakeling; he said he had lost his handkerchief, and seized the prisoner - the other ran away. Nobody else had been near us.</p>
